os Burning</span><hr size=1> It was time to begin gathering the forces. Time to start the planning. In order to take the city out they would need to work as one. Like a well oiled tinkered machine. They would need to move swiftly, and with stealth so as not the alert the enemy.<br>
Kat sat at her small table, Nospiratus across from her. Between them lay the map. It was well marked by them both. <br>
A descision was at hand. Should they first take out the northern part of the city? Or begin from deep within the southern part. Like a wound that festered from the inside out. <br>
&quot;If we move against the north first. There's a chance that one will make it to the south to warn of the coming attack. Giving them time to refortify themselves. However if we come from within and work our way out.. this point here could become a bottleneck.&quot; Kat pointed to the narrow ally they would have to go through to reach the north. <br>
&quot;Someone could slip past us and warn the north, They could then set up their ambush and bottleneck us in here.. Picking us off one at a time.&quot;<br>
&quot;My thoughts are to take out the North side first.. then disappear into the sewers instead of coming through this alley. The imbeciles would never think to watch for us there. We could either battle to this point here, where we had held our first foray? Or, we could use stealth to reach this point and with subterfuge slowly draw them into our web.&quot;<br>
She fell silent then looking up at him and waited for his input. &quot;We must do this soon Nospiratus, for this child will not wait till we are ready.&quot;<br>
Nospiratus nodded to her words, from his silence she knew he was mulling over all the aspects of this campaign. &quot;Word has reached me that Sir Lancelot will prove a daunting foe to us. Do we allow him to live Ma Vie? To take him we'll need our strongest warriors. And many of them. He has developed a strong immunity to all forms of magics. And his bite*,&quot; Nos shook his head,&quot; is ten times worse than his bark.&quot; <br>
Kat nodded at his words, &quot; This m'own we'll need to decide at the moment. It depends upon how many high ranking warriors we are able to bring with us. I would think those who know the way of discipline** will be needed to take him out. We'll also need clerics set up in a heal circle*** to continually keep the warrior who has his attention alive, till said warriors discipline is spent. At the same time.. we'll need one or two groups to handle any allies who may come to assist him.&quot;<br>
Nospiratus nodded at this, &quot;Aye Ma Vie, this will be no easy foe. We'll need to call not only upon the Chosen, but all our allies as well.&quot;<br>
&quot;Aye,&quot; she responded. &quot;Should we call others into our little planning session? Perhaps Vresk, Daiunus, Faeolin and Tzlar can shed some light upon this?&quot;<br>
Again he nodded, &quot;Aye them and Kasirath, Shaede and Zirrix as well.&quot; <br>
&quot;Aye m'own. We'll need all of them, if we are to successfuly take this city. And by Innoruuk's black heart. I mean to see Qeynos fall!&quot;<br>
&quot;Daiunus and Khasirath, i'm sure will be able to perhaps persuade our allies in joining us Ma Vie.&quot; Nos reassured her. &quot;That city will fall, for Innoruuk, and.. for us.&quot; <br>
She smiled at his words then stepped to the door to summon a servant. Word was sent then to those named to join herself and Nospiratus in confrence.<br>
&quot;Have you decided Ma Vie, what will be left standing?&quot; He asked her softly as she returned to sit beside him. &quot;Yes m'own, the bards guild, here.. &quot; She pointed to the spot on the map, &quot;It is out of our way, they shall be left to live. To tell of the Fall of Qeynos. To warn others that the reckoning is at hand. They will herald our deeds for years to come. But, &quot; she smiled up at him then, &quot; They will also be the ones to shelter our child. From them he shall learn many things. With them he will find sanctuary.&quot; Nos nodded to her words, his hand moving to give her own a gentle squeeze. <br>
&quot;When the others arrive Ma Vie, let me handle them. You are not exactly a diplomat, &quot; he chuckled softly as she grinned impishly at him. They both fell silent then waiting.. for the others. <br>
